`QueryOption::default().with_enable_storage_read(true)` enables storage read API for query.

#177 

```rust
async fn run(client: &Client, project_id: &str) {
    let request = QueryRequest {
             query: "SELECT * FROM dataset.table".to_string(),
            ..Default::default()
    };
    let option = QueryOption::default().with_enable_storage_read(true);
    let mut iter = client.query_with_option::<Row>(project_id, request, option).await.unwrap();
     while let Some(row) = iter.next().await.unwrap() {
         let col1 = row.column::<String>(0);
         let col2 = row.column::<Option<String>>(1);
     }
}
```

Added `google-cloud-default`'s `WithAuthExt` as a feature of each component.(features=["auth"])

## How to migrate
* Remove `google-cloud-default` . 
   Since auth is also the default feature, `features=["auth"]` is required only when the default feature is disabled, such as when using `rustls-tls`.
```toml
google-cloud-storage = { version="xxx", default-features=false, features=["rustls-tls","auth"]}
google-cloud-bigquery = { version="xxx", default-features=false, features=["rustls-tls","auth"]}
```

* Remove google_cloud_default from code. interface is not changed.
```rust
use google_cloud_pubsub::client::{ClientConfig, Client};
// use google_cloud_default::WithAuthExt;  <- remove dependency

async fn run() {
     let config = ClientConfig::default().with_auth().await.unwrap();
     let client = Client::new(config).await.unwrap();
}
```

